# tests/fuzz-corpus/arith/corpus.jsonl
#
# Permanent regression corpus for the DIV-class arithmetic differential
# fuzzer (Phase 3 / R-E1). One JSON object per line:
#   {"op","a","b","n","expected"}   (hex; n used only by mulmod/addmod)
#
# `expected` is the execution-specs *amsterdam* oracle's verdict, produced
# by scripts/fuzz_arith_oracle.py. The PR fast-path
# (scripts/fuzz-arith-diff.sh) re-runs EvmWord.{div,mod,sdiv,smod,mulmod,
# addmod} on each entry and asserts it still equals `expected` — a frozen
# cross-implementation check that needs no Python at PR time. The nightly
# `--python` tier APPENDS every newly-discovered divergence here so it can
# never silently regress.
#
# Seed entries are the curated DIV-class edge cases (zero divisor, 4-limb
# divisors with a large top word — the b.getLimbN 3 != 0 regime the v4 DIV
# proof EXCLUDED — Knuth add-back, the SDIV signed-overflow point
# -2^255 / -1, sign edges, N=0, and >256-bit-precision MULMOD/ADDMOD).
# Comment lines (#) and blank lines are ignored by the reader.
{"op":"div","a":"0x0","b":"0x0","n":"0x0","expected":"0x0"}
